                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">1. Understanding Capacity: What mAh Really Means</h2>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">The most important number on a power bank — and the most misunderstood. Here's what mAh actually means for your phone.</p>

                    <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
                        <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3">Rated vs Usable Capacity: The 60-70% Rule</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-4">Power bank capacity is measured at the internal battery voltage of <strong>3.7V</strong>, but USB output requires <strong>5V or higher</strong>. During this voltage step-up conversion, energy is lost as heat. The result: you only get about <strong>60-70% of the rated capacity</strong> as usable output.</p>
                        <div class="bg-brandBlue/5 rounded-xl p-5 border border-brandBlue/10 mb-4">
                            <p class="font-black text-brandBlue text-sm uppercase mb-2">The Conversion Formula</p>
                            <p class="text-slate-700 font-mono text-sm"><strong>Usable mAh = (Rated mAh × 3.7V × Efficiency) ÷ 5V</strong></p>
                            <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs mt-2">Example: 10,000mAh × 3.7V × 0.85 ÷ 5V = <strong>~6,290mAh usable</strong></p>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Premium power banks with GaN technology achieve 85-92% conversion efficiency. Budget models typically manage 60-75%. This is why two "10,000mAh" power banks can deliver noticeably different real-world performance. For a deeper technical breakdown, read our <a href="/blog/power-bank-specs-guide/" class="text-brandBlue hover:underline">Power Bank Specs Guide</a>.</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
                        <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-4">How Many Phone Charges Will I Get?</h3>
                        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                            <table class="w-full border border-slate-200 rounded-xl">
                                <thead class="bg-brandBlue text-white">
                                    <tr>
                                        <th class="text-left p-3 font-black uppercase text-xs">Phone Battery</th>
                                        <th class="text-center p-3 font-black uppercase text-xs">5,000mAh Bank</th>
                                        <th class="text-center p-3 font-black uppercase text-xs">10,000mAh Bank</th>
                                        <th class="text-center p-3 font-black uppercase text-xs">20,000mAh Bank</th>
                                    </tr>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody>
                                    <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="p-3 font-bold text-sm">iPhone 15/16 (~3,300mAh)</td><td class="p-3 text-center">~1 charge</td><td class="p-3 text-center text-brandBlue font-bold">~1.5-2 charges</td><td class="p-3 text-center">~3.5-4 charges</td></tr>
                                    <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="p-3 font-bold text-sm">iPhone 16 Pro Max (~4,500mAh)</td><td class="p-3 text-center">~0.7 charges</td><td class="p-3 text-center text-brandBlue font-bold">~1.2-1.5 charges</td><td class="p-3 text-center">~2.5-3 charges</td></tr>
                                    <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="p-3 font-bold text-sm">Galaxy S25 Ultra (5,000mAh)</td><td class="p-3 text-center">~0.6 charges</td><td class="p-3 text-center text-brandBlue font-bold">~1.1-1.3 charges</td><td class="p-3 text-center">~2.3-2.6 charges</td></tr>
                                    <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="p-3 font-bold text-sm">Pixel 9 Pro (~4,700mAh)</td><td class="p-3 text-center">~0.7 charges</td><td class="p-3 text-center text-brandBlue font-bold">~1.2-1.4 charges</td><td class="p-3 text-center">~2.5-3 charges</td></tr>
                                    <tr><td class="p-3 font-bold text-sm">iPad Air (~7,500mAh)</td><td class="p-3 text-center">❌ Not practical</td><td class="p-3 text-center">~0.7 charges</td><td class="p-3 text-center text-brandBlue font-bold">~1.5-2 charges</td></tr>
                                </tbody>
                            </table>
                        </div>
                        <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs mt-3">*Assumes 65% conversion efficiency. Actual results vary with temperature, cable quality, and device charging behavior.</p>
                    </div>
