                <section id="capacity-tiers" class="mb-16">
                    <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">2. Capacity Tiers: 5,000 to 27,000mAh Compared</h2>
                    <div class="space-y-6">
                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
                                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 text-xs font-black rounded-full">5,000mAh</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">~100-150g · Keychain/credit-card sized</span>
                            </div>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Emergency top-ups, nights out, glove box backup. Provides ~0.5-1 phone charge.</p>
                            <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs">⚠️ Not suitable for heavy users, travel, or multi-device charging. The main advantage is extreme portability — some models are as thin as 6.8mm using <a href="/blog/semi-solid-state-power-bank-oem/" class="text-brandBlue hover:underline">semi-solid-state battery</a> technology.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6 border-2 border-brandOrange/30">
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
                                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-brandOrange text-white text-xs font-black rounded-full">10,000mAh ★ RECOMMENDED</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">~180-250g · Pocket-sized</span>
                            </div>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Daily commuters, students, office workers — the sweet spot for most people. Provides ~1.5-2 phone charges.</p>
                            <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs">This is the most popular capacity tier globally (47.89% market share). It balances portability and capacity perfectly — fits in a pocket or small bag, delivers enough power for a full day's top-up, and costs $20-40 for a quality model. If you're buying your first power bank, start here.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
                                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 text-xs font-black rounded-full">20,000mAh</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">~350-500g · Small book-sized</span>
                            </div>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Travelers, families, content creators, multi-device users. Provides ~3-4 phone charges.</p>
                            <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs">At 74Wh, this is well within airline carry-on limits (100Wh max). Can partially charge tablets and small ultrabooks. The added weight is noticeable — you'll carry this in a bag, not a pocket. Worth it for weekend trips and long days away from outlets.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
                                <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-slate-100 text-slate-600 text-xs font-black rounded-full">27,000mAh+</span>
                                <span class="text-xs text-slate-400">~500-650g · Large phone-sized</span>
                            </div>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mb-2"><strong>Best for:</strong> Laptop charging, multi-day outdoor trips, professional use. Can charge a MacBook Air once.</p>
                            <p class="text-slate-500 text-xs">⚠️ At ~99.9Wh, this is right at the 100Wh airline limit. Anything larger requires airline approval or is prohibited. Only buy this tier if you specifically need laptop charging capability. For most users, 10,000-20,000mAh is the practical maximum.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
