                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">4. Ports & Connectivity: USB-C, USB-A, and Wireless</h2>
                    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
                            <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3">USB-C (Recommended)</h3>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">The modern standard. Supports PD fast charging, data transfer, and video output. In 2026, USB-C is mandatory for new devices sold in the EU. For power banks, USB-C should handle both input (recharging the bank) and output (charging devices). Look for <strong>bi-directional USB-C</strong> with PD 3.0/3.1 support. Read our <a href="/blog/usb-c-pd-fast-charging-guide/" class="text-brandBlue hover:underline">USB-C PD Fast Charging Guide</a> for cable recommendations.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
                            <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3">USB-A (Legacy)</h3>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">The traditional rectangular port. Still useful for charging older devices, wireless earbuds cases, and accessories that use USB-A to Micro-USB cables. Most power banks include at least one USB-A port for backward compatibility. Output is typically limited to 10-18W.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
                            <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3">Qi2 Wireless / Magnetic</h3>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Qi2 magnetic power banks snap onto the back of your phone (iPhone 12+ and Qi2-compatible Android). Convenient for cable-free top-ups, but less efficient — <strong>70-80% charging efficiency</strong> vs 85-92% for wired, and more heat generation. Qi2.2 (25W) is the latest standard. Not ideal as a primary power bank, but excellent as a secondary daily-carry option. See our <a href="/blog/qi2-vs-magsafe-guide/" class="text-brandBlue hover:underline">Qi2 vs MagSafe Guide</a>.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-6">
                            <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3">Built-in Cables</h3>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Some power banks integrate USB-C and/or Lightning cables directly into the housing. Extremely convenient — no cable to forget — but limits flexibility. If the built-in cable wears out, the entire power bank may need replacement. Look for models with <strong>reinforced strain relief</strong> on built-in cables.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section id="features" class="mb-16">
                    <div class="bg-slate-50 rounded-xl p-6 border border-slate-200 shadow-sm">
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">5. Must-Have Features in 2026</h2>
                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5">
                            <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-2">GaN (Gallium Nitride) Technology</h3>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">GaN power banks are smaller, cooler, and more efficient (90-92% conversion vs 80-85%). The size difference is significant — a GaN 10,000mAh bank is noticeably slimmer. Worth the modest premium. <a href="/blog/what-is-gan-charger/" class="text-brandBlue hover:underline">Learn more about GaN →</a></p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5">
                            <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-2">Digital Battery Display</h3>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">LED dots (4 lights = 25% each) are imprecise. A digital percentage display tells you exactly how much power remains — critical when deciding whether to bring the bank or charge it before leaving. Look for LCD or TFT displays showing both percentage and charging wattage.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5">
                            <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-2">Pass-Through Charging</h3>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Can the power bank charge your devices while being recharged itself? This is essential for overnight use — plug the bank into the wall, plug your phone into the bank, and both are full by morning. Not all power banks support this; verify before buying.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl p-5">
                            <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-2">Semi-Solid-State Battery</h3>
                            <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">The newest battery technology: gel electrolyte replaces most of the flammable liquid in traditional Li-ion cells. Benefits include <strong>2-3× longer lifespan</strong> (1,000-2,000 cycles), <strong>dramatically safer</strong> (no fire when punctured), and <strong>ultra-thin designs</strong> (as thin as 6.8mm). Premium price but genuinely better technology. <a href="/blog/semi-solid-state-power-bank-oem/" class="text-brandBlue hover:underline">Read our semi-solid-state guide →</a></p>
                        </div>
